ANATOMY OF THE MAIN ENTRY.

BASIC INTRODUCTION TO THE CONCEPT OF MAIN ENTRY IN CATALOGUING-THE NAME OR
TERM UNDER WHICH THE WORK IS PRIMARILY ENTERED BOTH ON A CATALOGUE CARD AND IN
A BIBLIOGRAPHY. DESCRIBES THE IMPRINT, COLLATION, PAGINATION, ILLUSTRATIONS,
SIZE AND NOTES AND THEIR RELATIONSHIP TO THE MAIN ENTRY IN CATALOGUING.
